{
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we aim to make the first attempt to operationalize one principle of \"right to protect data\" into algorithmic implementation in practice, i.e., people having control over their online data, and propose REGTEXT, an approach to transform any text dataset into an unlearnable one.",
    "Formally, an unlearnable dataset, when input to a learning algorithm, results in a model that fails to generalize to the corresponding test set during inference.",
    "Notably, there has been limited progress in for-mally establishing a framework for generating unlearnable text data.",
    "Existing approaches primarily exhibit three significant practical limitations: i) are model-dependent, ii) lack scalability, and iii) rely on time-inefficient and unstable, gradientbased methods (Ren et al., 2023; Zhang et al., 2023; Huang et al., 2021; Li et al., 2023).",
    "While Li et al. (2023) adapts the optimization framework for images introduced by Huang et al. (2021) for text data, it still relies on a bi-level optimization approach which is computationally expensive."
  ]
}